---
import ToolPage from '../layouts/ToolPage.astro';
---
<ToolPage
  title="AI Architecture Generator (BYO key), describe an app, get an architecture | KB Cafe"
  description="Describe what you want to build and get a clear architecture (components, data flow, risks, MVP), not code. Brings your own OpenAI or Anthropic key, stored only in your browser."
  path="/ai-architecture-generator"
  eyebrow="AI Explained · Tool · BYO key"
  h1="AI Architecture Generator"
  tagline="Describe what you want to build and get a clear architecture back, components, data flow, risks, and an MVP cut, not code. Uses your own API key, kept in your browser and sent only to your provider."
>
  <div class="ag-key">
    <div class="row ag-prov" id="prov">
      <button class="chip active" data-p="openai">OpenAI</button>
      <button class="chip" data-p="anthropic">Anthropic</button>
    </div>
    <div class="ag-keyrow">
      <input id="key" type="password" placeholder="sk-… (your API key)" autocomplete="off" />
      <input id="model" type="text" class="ag-model" />
      <button class="link-btn" id="forget">forget</button>
    </div>
    <p class="ag-keynote">🔒 Your key is stored only in <strong>this browser</strong> (localStorage) and sent <strong>directly to your provider</strong>, never to KB Cafe. You pay your provider for the call.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="pane">
    <div class="pane-label"><span>What do you want to build?</span><button class="link-btn" id="sample">sample</button></div>
    <textarea id="desc" class="ta" spellcheck="false" placeholder="e.g. A site where users upload PDFs and ask questions about them, with accounts and a free tier…"></textarea>
  </div>
  <div class="row" style="margin:14px 0"><button class="btn" id="gen">Generate architecture</button><span class="ag-status" id="status"></span></div>

  <div class="ag-out" id="out" hidden></div>

  <Fragment slot="explainer">
    <h2>Architecture, not code</h2>
    <p>
      Before you write a line, the useful question is <em>what are the pieces and how do they connect?</em> This
      tool takes a plain description and returns an <strong>architecture</strong>, the frontend, backend, storage,
      any <a href="/what-is-rag">retrieval</a> layer, auth, the data flow, the risks, and a minimal first version,
      so you can see the shape of the system. It deliberately doesn&rsquo;t write code; the value is the map, not
      the bricks.
    </p>
    <h3>Why bring your own key</h3>
    <p>
      This is the one tool here that calls a real model, so it needs a key. KB Cafe stays true to its rule by
      keeping it <strong>yours</strong>: the key lives in your browser and the request goes straight to OpenAI or
      Anthropic, never through our servers. We never see your key, your prompt, or the output, and you only pay
      your provider&rsquo;s normal rate.
    </p>
    <p class="note">
      Because the call is browser-to-provider, the prompt that powers this is visible in the page, that&rsquo;s the
      honest trade for a no-backend, no-cost-to-you design. Get a key from your provider&rsquo;s dashboard; a small,
      cheap model is plenty for an architecture sketch.
    </p>

    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <details class="faq"><summary>Does KB Cafe see my key or data?</summary>
      <p>No. The key is in your browser&rsquo;s localStorage and the request goes directly to your provider&rsquo;s API. Nothing routes through KB Cafe, there&rsquo;s no backend here at all.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq"><summary>Why architecture instead of code?</summary>
      <p>The hard part of building isn&rsquo;t typing, it&rsquo;s deciding the components and how data flows. A good architecture sketch makes the code obvious and catches problems early.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq"><summary>What does it cost?</summary>
      <p>Whatever your provider charges for the tokens, usually a fraction of a cent on a small model. Estimate it with the <a href="/llm-cost-calculator">Cost Calculator</a>.</p>
    </details>

    <h3>Related</h3>
    <p>Design the agent flow in the <a href="/ai-pattern-builder">Pattern Builder</a>, map the concepts with the <a href="/ai-stack-explainer">Stack Explainer</a>, or browse <a href="/ai">AI Explained</a>.</p>
  </Fragment>
</ToolPage>

<style>
  .link-btn{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--coral);background:none;border:0;cursor:pointer}
  .link-btn:hover{color:var(--coral-deep);text-decoration:underline}
  .ag-key{border:1.5px solid var(--line);border-radius:14px;background:var(--cream);padding:15px 16px;margin-bottom:18px}
  .ag-prov{margin-bottom:11px}
  .ag-keyrow{display:flex;gap:10px;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap}
  .ag-keyrow input{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:13.5px;border:1.5px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px;padding:9px 12px;background:var(--paper);color:var(--ink);outline:0}
  #key{flex:1;min-width:200px} .ag-model{width:200px}
  .ag-keyrow input:focus{border-color:var(--ink)}
  .ag-keynote{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:11.5px;color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.5;margin:10px 0 0}
  .ta{min-height:120px}
  .ag-status{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:12.5px;color:var(--ink-soft)}
  .ag-out{border:1.5px solid var(--line);border-radius:16px;background:var(--cream);padding:20px 22px;line-height:1.6}
  .ag-out h3{font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:800;font-size:19px;margin:18px 0 8px;letter-spacing:-.02em}
  .ag-out h3:first-child{margin-top:0}
  .ag-out h4{font-family:var(--font-display);font-weight:800;font-size:15px;margin:14px 0 5px}
  .ag-out p{margin:0 0 10px;color:var(--ink)}
  .ag-out ul,.ag-out ol{margin:0 0 12px;padding-left:22px}
  .ag-out li{margin-bottom:4px;color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.5}
  .ag-out strong{color:var(--ink)}
  .ag-out code{font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:12.5px;background:var(--paper-2);padding:1px 5px;border-radius:5px}
</style>

<script is:inline>
  const $ = (id) => document.getElementById(id);
  const DEFAULTS = { openai: 'gpt-4o-mini', anthropic: 'claude-3-5-sonnet-latest' };
  let prov = 'openai';
  const SYS = "You are a senior software architect. Given a product description, output a clear ARCHITECTURE, not code. Use markdown with these sections: ## Overview, ## Components (cover Frontend, Backend, Storage/DB, AI / Retrieval if relevant, Auth, Integrations), ## Data flow (a numbered list), ## Key risks, ## MVP scope (the smallest first version). Be concrete and concise. Do NOT write code or commands.";
  const SAMPLE = "A web app where users upload PDFs and ask questions about them in a chat. Accounts with a free tier (3 PDFs) and a paid tier. Answers should cite the source page.";

  function keyId() { return 'kbcafe-key-' + prov; }
  function loadKey() { try { $('key').value = localStorage.getItem(keyId()) || ''; } catch {} $('model').value = DEFAULTS[prov]; }
  function saveKey() { try { localStorage.setItem(keyId(), $('key').value.trim()); } catch {} }

  // tiny markdown renderer (headings, bold, lists, paragraphs)
  function md(src) {
    const esc = (s) => s.replace(/&/g, '&amp;').replace(/</g, '&lt;').replace(/>/g, '&gt;');
    const lines = esc(src).split('\n'); let html = '', list = '';
    const closeList = () => { if (list) { html += `<${list.tag}>${list.items}</${list.tag}>`; list = ''; } };
    lines.forEach(raw => {
      let l = raw.replace(/\*\*([^*]+)\*\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>').replace(/`([^`]+)`/g, '<code>$1</code>');
      if (/^###?\s+/.test(raw)) { closeList(); const lvl = raw.startsWith('### ') ? 'h4' : 'h3'; html += `<${lvl}>${l.replace(/^#+\s+/, '')}</${lvl}>`; }
      else if (/^\s*[-*]\s+/.test(raw)) { if (!list || list.tag !== 'ul') { closeList(); list = { tag: 'ul', items: '' }; } list.items += `<li>${l.replace(/^\s*[-*]\s+/, '')}</li>`; }
      else if (/^\s*\d+\.\s+/.test(raw)) { if (!list || list.tag !== 'ol') { closeList(); list = { tag: 'ol', items: '' }; } list.items += `<li>${l.replace(/^\s*\d+\.\s+/, '')}</li>`; }
      else if (raw.trim() === '') { closeList(); }
      else { closeList(); html += `<p>${l}</p>`; }
    });
    closeList(); return html;
  }

  async function generate() {
    const key = $('key').value.trim(), model = $('model').value.trim() || DEFAULTS[prov], desc = $('desc').value.trim();
    if (!key) { $('status').textContent = 'Enter your API key first.'; return; }
    if (!desc) { $('status').textContent = 'Describe what you want to build.'; return; }
    saveKey(); $('gen').disabled = true; $('status').textContent = 'Generating…'; $('out').hidden = true;
    try {
      let text;
      if (prov === 'openai') {
        const r = await fetch('https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions', {
          method: 'POST', headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'Authorization': 'Bearer ' + key },
          body: JSON.stringify({ model, temperature: 0.4, messages: [{ role: 'system', content: SYS }, { role: 'user', content: desc }] }),
        });
        const d = await r.json();
        if (!r.ok) throw new Error(d.error ? d.error.message : ('HTTP ' + r.status));
        text = d.choices[0].message.content;
      } else {
        const r = await fetch('https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages', {
          method: 'POST', headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json', 'x-api-key': key, 'anthropic-version': '2023-06-01', 'anthropic-dangerous-direct-browser-access': 'true' },
          body: JSON.stringify({ model, max_tokens: 1800, system: SYS, messages: [{ role: 'user', content: desc }] }),
        });
        const d = await r.json();
        if (!r.ok) throw new Error(d.error ? d.error.message : ('HTTP ' + r.status));
        text = d.content[0].text;
      }
      $('out').innerHTML = md(text); $('out').hidden = false; $('status').textContent = 'Done. (You paid your provider for this call.)';
    } catch (e) {
      $('status').textContent = 'Error: ' + ((e && e.message) || 'request failed') + '. Check the key, model name, and your provider account.';
    } finally { $('gen').disabled = false; }
  }

  $('prov').addEventListener('click', (e) => { const b = e.target.closest('.chip'); if (!b) return; document.querySelectorAll('#prov .chip').forEach(c => c.classList.remove('active')); b.classList.add('active'); prov = b.dataset.p; loadKey(); });
  $('key').addEventListener('change', saveKey);
  $('forget').addEventListener('click', () => { try { localStorage.removeItem(keyId()); } catch {} $('key').value = ''; $('status').textContent = 'Key forgotten.'; });
  $('sample').addEventListener('click', () => { $('desc').value = SAMPLE; });
  $('gen').addEventListener('click', generate);
  loadKey();
</script>
